extra_descr_data.keyword: paper wad newbie pad manual book
extra_descr_data.description:
This shiney new book tells you some usefull hints on how to begin here:

o Kill the dinosaurs' first (there are several down) they are very     o
o easy and have some EQ.                                               o
o Always read signs if they are there. They always give you help here. o
o When you begin to get XP train your 'Int' before you practice spells o
o as it saves you XP.  The following spells are reccomended :          o

	Clot	mend	heal	soulblade	regen	  'dispel magic'	 

o Always use a stance, the more you use them the more they improve.    o
o If you need more help on anything mentioned try 'help word' Where    o
o word is the word you desire help on, e.g 'help stances'.             o
o                                                                      o
o See also: help NEWBIE, BASICS, and BASICSPELLS                       o

rooms.name: Dark Forest
rooms.description:
Tall trees and heavy foliage surround completely.  The tree canopy is so 
dense that ti allows no light through to the forest floor.  The trail 
extends further east still.

rooms.name: Light forest
rooms.description:
Small trees and light shrubery surround you here.  Light filters freely 
from above through the thin layering of treetops.  The trail extends east 
but seems to get darker.

rooms.name: Rough shrubland
rooms.description:
Clumps of rough looking shrubbery crunch underfoot as you walk, they seem 
to spring up from everywhere here.  Some small thorn bushes and thistles 
grow here also.

rooms.name: A drinking hole
rooms.description:
A rather large pond has been formed here.  Some HUGE footprints lead from 
the shrubery into the pond, I wonder what made those?

rooms.name: Dusty trail
rooms.description:
The wind blows and dust swirls up around you.  You find yourself walking a 
dusty trail.

rooms.name: Plateau
rooms.description:
You stand atop a high plateau looking down over the plains and forests 
below, its a truly dazzling view.  You can just hear the gush of the river
Ob flowing below.

rooms.name: Rocky outcropping
rooms.description:
You find yourself treading precariously over a crevasse, better watch your 
step!

rooms.name: A nest!
rooms.description:
You have stumbled into the middle of some HUGE beasts nest!!!!
Is it time to leave you wonder?

rooms.name: The Centre Room.
rooms.description:
Four pens surround you, each contains a poor Dinosaur
which Merlin the evil wizard has imprisoned here to
test his nasty potions on!

extra_descr_data.description:
Welcome to the Maekon Dungeons, this is where some evil mage keeps small 
fluffy Dinosaurs to test his potions and spells on!  Kill them and spare 
them from this misery.   Kill them all!

After you kill each dinosaur, get all of the equipment from their corpses
with the command 'GET whatever CORPSE'.  You can then use the command 'WEAR 
ALL' to wear your newly won equipment.

When you are done with the corpse, 'SACRIFICE CORPSE' to give it to your God.
God will reward you for this.

Between combat, you may need to rest or sleep to regenerate hit points.
You can 'REST' to regenerate hit points, or you can 'SLEEP'.  'SLEEP' will
refresh you faster than 'REST', but you will be less aware of your
surroundings.

rooms.name: The North Cage.
rooms.description:
You are in the northern cage of the Dungeon.
A poor dinosaur is chained to the wall in the corner.
The only exit is south.

A poor dinosaur is chained to the wall in the corner.
The only exit is east.

rooms.name: The Southern cave.
rooms.description:

The only exit is north.

rooms.name: The Eastern cave.
rooms.description:
You are in the eastern cage of the Dungeon. 
A poor dinosaur is chained to the wall in the corner.
The only exit is west.

rooms.name: Pit of the Damned.
rooms.description:
You have wandered into the dungeons' lower levels.
You are surrounded by the Souls of the Damned. These
wretched creatures are the spiritual remains of the
Tortured Dinosaurs tested on by Merlin the evil mage!
The only exit is up.

rooms.name: A T-Junction in the trail
rooms.description:
The trail fawks off to the north and west here.  The northern trail 
seems to wind up a hill to a mountain, and the western path appears 
to open into light scrub land.

A sign hangs here from a blood stained post.

extra_descr_data.description:
[north] :
Gondmaeglom lies to the north, the mountain fort is accessible via a hilly path leading through the mountains.  This area is rumoured to be inhabited by evil mages, beware!

[west] :
Dol-Guldur lies in the open plains to the south west beyond the scrub lands of the west.  This area is rumoured to be ruled by GIANT beasts, beware!

Dinosaur names can be shortened ; e.g maliusaurus can be shortened to mali.
        brontosaurus to bronto etc..  They ALL have short hand names :)

Finally you find yourself at the top of this raggid path.  As you look down 
behind you the magniude of the height you have scaled hits you!  You must be 
a thousand feet up!
You see some kind of stone structure to the north.

rooms.name: A dark cave

rooms.name: A dark and damp cave
rooms.description:
It is very dark and smelly in here.  In fact it's REALLY very smelly here, 
I wonder what your standing in?

rooms.name: Dead-End!
rooms.description:
Cracks in the ceiling of the cave allow some slithers of light in, you can 
barely make out what the cause of that terrible smell is, You are standing 
in what is left of the mouldering remains of several people.
Some ancient markings are engraved on the wall here.

extra_descr_data.description:
The ancient markings tell the story of an ancient and simplistic tribe of 
warriors who hunted a band of men of 'fire and air'.  This story tells of 
how they chased the mages, draining them of their magical energy and finally
cornered them here.  It describes how mages uttered some strange words and 
just vanished!!!

This carving is a reminder to their decendants so that one day they may 
catch one.

"Whobat thobe fobuck" is written below it also.
